        "# IF240 - Apprentissage et deep learning\n",
        "\n",
        "## Practice 3: SVM \n",
        "\n",
        "By Aur√©lie Bugeau\n",
        "Credits:  Vincent Lepetit"
      ]
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "markdown",
      "metadata": {
        "id": "2xGFdizNJ7q9"
      },
      "source": [
        "    ### Objectives\n",
        "The objective of the practice is to apply SVM with different kernels. You will use the two folling 2 moons and 2 circles datasets."
      ]
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "code",
      "metadata": {
        "id": "MR4ghvfIJ7q-",
        "outputId": "d3790735-185a-40e1-c464-d7553f29f8bd",
        "colab": {
          "base_uri": "https://localhost:8080/",
          "height": 513
        }
      },
      "source": [
        "from sklearn.datasets import make_moons, make_circles\n",
        "%matplotlib inline\n",
        "import matplotlib.pyplot as plt\n",
        "\n",
        "moons_X,moons_y = make_moons(1500, noise=.05, random_state=0)\n",
        "circles_X,circles_y = make_circles(1500, factor=.5, noise=.05)\n",
        "\n",
        "plt.scatter(moons_X[:, 0], moons_X[:, 1], c=moons_y,s=50, cmap='viridis');\n",
        "plt.show()\n",
        "plt.scatter(circles_X[:, 0], circles_X[:, 1], c=circles_y,s=50, cmap='viridis');\n"
      ],
      "execution_count": 18,
      "outputs": [
        {
          "output_type": "display_data",
          "data": {

            "text/plain": [
              "<Figure size 432x288 with 1 Axes>"

        {

    {
      "cell_type": "markdown",
      "metadata": {
        "id": "fuWSZoOxJ7rC"
      },
      "source": [
        "### Question 1\n",
        "Make sure you understand what _Xmoons_, _ymoons_, _Xcircles_, _ycircles_ contain exactly"
      ]
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "markdown",
      "metadata": {
        "id": "VxfQjhqcJ7rD"
      },
      "source": [
        "Separate the data into training and test data with:"
      ]
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "code",
      "metadata": {
        "id": "QE0MdVsvJ7rE"
      },
      "source": [
        "import numpy as np\n",
        "indices = np.random.permutation(len(moons_X))\n",
        "moons_X_train = moons_X[indices[:-40]]\n",
        "moons_y_train = moons_y[indices[:-40]]\n",
        "moons_X_valid = moons_X[indices[-40:-20]]\n",
        "moons_y_valid = moons_y[indices[-40:-20]]\n",
        "moons_X_test  = moons_X[indices[-20:]]\n",
        "moons_y_test  = moons_y[indices[-20:]]"
      ],
      "execution_count": 19,
      "outputs": []
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "code",
      "metadata": {
        "id": "La6w4zSQJ7rG"
      },
      "source": [
        "circles_X_train = circles_X[indices[:-40]]\n",
        "circles_y_train = circles_y[indices[:-40]]\n",
        "circles_X_valid = circles_X[indices[-40:-20]]\n",
        "circles_y_valid = circles_y[indices[-40:-20]]\n",
        "circles_X_test  = circles_X[indices[-20:]]\n",
        "circles_y_test  = circles_y[indices[-20:]]"
      ],
      "execution_count": 20,
      "outputs": []
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "markdown",
      "metadata": {
        "id": "2hSMwt8WJ7rJ"
      },
      "source": [
        "## Linear SVM\n",
        "### Question 2\n",
        "Apply linear SVM to these data and print the accuracy on the test datasets."
      ]
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "code",
      "metadata": {
        "id": "xS0XJNWJJ7rK",
        "outputId": "7330dcd7-4734-4028-a98b-11f6ad8afccf",
        "colab": {
          "base_uri": "https://localhost:8080/"
        }
      },
      "source": [
        "from sklearn import svm\n",
        "svc_moon = svm.SVC(kernel='linear')\n",
        "svc_moon.fit(moons_X_train,moons_y_train)\n",
        "\n",
        "svc_circle = svm.SVC(kernel='linear')\n",
        "svc_circle.fit(circles_X_train,circles_y_train)"
      ],
      "execution_count": 21,
      "outputs": [
        {
          "output_type": "execute_result",
          "data": {
            "text/plain": [
              "SVC(C=1.0, break_ties=False, cache_size=200, class_weight=None, coef0=0.0,\n",
              "    decision_function_shape='ovr', degree=3, gamma='scale', kernel='linear',\n",
              "    max_iter=-1, probability=False, random_state=None, shrinking=True,\n",
              "    tol=0.001, verbose=False)"
            ]
          },
          "metadata": {
            "tags": []
          },
          "execution_count": 21
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "markdown",
      "metadata": {
        "id": "umdHcJ9jJ7rM"
      },
      "source": [
        "### Question 3\n",
        "Check the documentation at \\url{http://scikit-learn.org/stable/modules/generated/sklearn.svm.SVC.html#sklearn.svm.SVC} to see how to change the parameter $C$, the weight between the classification score and the regularization term.\n",
        "\n",
        "Use the validation sets to identify the optimal value for $C$ and print the value of the corresponding on the test set."
      ]
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "code",
      "metadata": {
        "id": "JqNH-voSJ7rN",
        "outputId": "ebfbf093-5a3f-4e1c-d3bd-192a4449b943",
        "colab": {
          "base_uri": "https://localhost:8080/"
        }
      },
      "source": [
        "X = [10**x for x in range(-3,3)]\n",
        "params = {'C': X}\n",
        "\n",
        "for k, v in params.items():\n",
        "    for val in v:\n",
        "        svc_moon = svm.SVC(kernel='linear')\n",
        "        svc_moon.fit(moons_X_train,moons_y_train)\n",
        "        svc_circle = svm.SVC(kernel='linear')\n",
        "        svc_circle.fit(circles_X_train,circles_y_train)\n",
        "        clf_moon = svc_moon.set_params(**{k: val})\n",
        "        clf_circle = svc_circle.set_params(**{k: val})\n",
        "\n",
        "        print(\"For C = \",val,\":\")\n",
        "        print(\"Moon Accuracy : \",clf_moon.score(moons_X_valid,moons_y_valid))\n",
        "        print(\"Circle Accuracy : \",clf_circle.score(circles_X_valid,circles_y_valid))\n",
        "        print()"
      ],
      "execution_count": 22,
      "outputs": [
        {
          "output_type": "stream",
          "text": [
            "For C =  0.001 :\n",
            "Moon Accuracy :  0.85\n",
            "Circle Accuracy :  0.5\n",
            "\n",
            "For C =  0.01 :\n",
            "Moon Accuracy :  0.85\n",
            "Circle Accuracy :  0.5\n",
            "\n",
            "For C =  0.1 :\n",
            "Moon Accuracy :  0.85\n",
            "Circle Accuracy :  0.5\n",
            "\n",
            "For C =  1 :\n",
            "Moon Accuracy :  0.85\n",
            "Circle Accuracy :  0.5\n",
            "\n",
            "For C =  10 :\n",
            "Moon Accuracy :  0.85\n",
            "Circle Accuracy :  0.5\n",
            "\n",
            "For C =  100 :\n",
            "Moon Accuracy :  0.85\n",
            "Circle Accuracy :  0.5\n",
            "\n"
          ],
          "name": "stdout"
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "markdown",
      "metadata": {
        "id": "zVjdNa92J7rP"
      },
      "source": [
        "### Question 4\n",
        "Let us visualize the result. For visualizing in 2D  the effect of an SVM classifier, you are given the following functions"
      ]
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "code",
      "metadata": {
        "id": "n8n5wh3CJ7rQ"
      },
      "source": [
        "import matplotlib.pyplot as plt\n",
        "\n",
        "\n",
        "def make_meshgrid(x, y, h=.02):\n",
        "    \"\"\"Create a mesh of points to plot in\n",
        "    \n",
        "    Parameters\n",
        "    ----------\n",
        "    x: data to base x-axis meshgrid on\n",
        "    y: data to base y-axis meshgrid on\n",
        "    h: stepsize for meshgrid, optional\n",
        "    Returns\n",
        "    -------\n",
        "    xx, yy : ndarray\n",
        "    \"\"\"\n",
        "    x_min, x_max = x.min() - 1, x.max() + 1\n",
        "    y_min, y_max = y.min() - 1, y.max() + 1\n",
        "    xx, yy = np.meshgrid(np.arange(x_min, x_max, h),\n",
        "                         np.arange(y_min, y_max, h))\n",
        "    return xx, yy\n",
        "\n",
        "\n",
        "def plot_contours(ax, clf, xx, yy, **params):\n",
        "    \"\"\"Plot the decision boundaries for a classifier.\n",
        "\n",
        "    Parameters\n",
        "    ----------\n",
        "    ax: matplotlib axes object\n",
        "    clf: a classifier\n",
        "    xx: meshgrid ndarray\n",
        "    yy: meshgrid ndarray\n",
        "    params: dictionary of params to pass to contourf, optional\n",
        "    \"\"\"\n",
        "    Z = clf.predict(np.c_[xx.ravel(), yy.ravel()])\n",
        "    Z = Z.reshape(xx.shape)\n",
        "    out = ax.contourf(xx, yy, Z, **params)\n",
        "    return out\n",
        "\n"
      ],
      "execution_count": 23,
      "outputs": []
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "markdown",
      "metadata": {
        "id": "MJq3yV-sJ7rS"
      },
      "source": [
        "The visualization functions can be used in the following way. Classification of every point on the meshgrid is made. Explain the result"
      ]
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "code",
      "metadata": {
        "id": "IMqmG0G0J7rV",
        "outputId": "8bea2eb8-d4f9-4fd2-90a4-ac9cfbb21c25",
        "colab": {
          "base_uri": "https://localhost:8080/",
          "height": 278
        }
      },
      "source": [
        "Xtest=moons_X_train\n",
        "ytest=moons_y_train\n",
        "\n",
        "models = (svm.SVC(kernel='linear', C=1),\n",
        "          svm.SVC(kernel='linear', C=10))\n",
        "models = (clf.fit(Xtest, ytest) for clf in models)\n",
        "\n",
        "# title for the plots\n",
        "titles = ('SVC with linear kernel, C=1',\n",
        "          'SVC with linear kernel, C=10')\n",
        "\n",
        "# Set-up 2x2 grid for plotting.\n",
        "fig, sub = plt.subplots(1,2)\n",
        "plt.subplots_adjust(wspace=0.4, hspace=0.4)\n",
        "\n",
        "X0, X1 = Xtest[:, 0], Xtest[:, 1]\n",
        "xx, yy = make_meshgrid(X0, X1)\n",
        "\n",
        "for clf, title, ax in zip(models, titles, sub.flatten()):\n",
        "    plot_contours(ax, clf, xx, yy,\n",
        "                  cmap=plt.cm.coolwarm, alpha=0.8)\n",
        "    ax.scatter(X0, X1, c=ytest, cmap=plt.cm.coolwarm, s=20, edgecolors='k')\n",
        "    ax.set_xlim(xx.min(), xx.max())\n",
        "    ax.set_ylim(yy.min(), yy.max())\n",
        "    ax.set_xlabel('Sepal length')\n",
        "    ax.set_ylabel('Sepal width')\n",
        "    ax.set_xticks(())\n",
        "    ax.set_yticks(())\n",
        "    ax.set_title(title)\n",
        "\n",
        "plt.show()"
      ],
      "execution_count": 24,
      "outputs": [
        {
          "output_type": "display_data",
          "data": {
            "image/png": "\n",
            "text/plain": [
              "<Figure size 432x288 with 2 Axes>"
            ]
          },
          "metadata": {
            "tags": []
          }
        }
      ]
    },
    {

      "source": [
        "## Non-Linear SVM\n",

        "Next experiment with the polynomial kernel."
